  "mergedContent": "Identity: 40-year-old former headman of Lisle; skilled rider with possible military background from border proximity; knows Karsite features, tactics, old practices (blood magic ritual sacrifice); stoic, pragmatic, stubborn to point of self-destruction. State: Newly awakened immensely powerful Mage-Gift (unknown type, possibly Firestarting)—burned open mental channels cause white-hot agony, blurred vision; underwent four-day unconscious journey to Haven due to Gift-shock severity; now at Haven Healers' Collegium, unconscious but stable. Arc: Witnessed entire village destroyed and people carried off during bandit attack; memories of destruction still blocked/suppressed—doesn't yet fully accept he did it himself; gathered evidence (red robes hidden under bandit clothing, tracks toward Menmellith) suggesting organized Karsite sect; driven by duty to warn Haven despite trauma. Relationship with Senta: Chosen by her—bond snapped into place when their eyes locked; shifted from resistance ('insufferable horse,' called for mercy killing) to full acceptance and partnership (affectionate nuzzle, 'we face it together'); her unconditional love and mental bridges stabilized his fracturing mind enough to survive; their connection allows mind-speech though it pains his ragged channels; ordered her to knock him out if he loses control—accepts danger he poses. Believed Herald-Mages were historical fiction before this experience.",
  "canonicalName": null
}

